1. Let PhotoCard render itself and its photo
2. Reach into DOM and figure out height of photo
3. Set the height on State to get Component to re-render
4. When re-rendering, assign `grid-row-end` to make sure photo takes up appropriate space


VANILLA JAVASCRIPT
-DevTools Console
eg:
document.querySelector('img')
=> the first image tag on the screen with alt and src

document.querySelector('img').clientHeight
=> returns numerical value of how many pixels of space that image has to render correctly without overlap


DOM ACCESS VIA REACT
-Make use of React system called ref(reference)
-React Refs
  -Gives access to a single DOM element
  -Create refs in constructor, assign it to instance variables, then pass it to a particular JSX element
   as PROPs
